    "narrative": "For Ghost Ride the WHIP today, we are leaning heavily into the speed and platoon profile of **Mickey Moniak**, who stands as our highest-rated start at 75.75. Facing the volatile V\u00e1squez, R (5.43 xERA), **Mickey Moniak** benefits from a massive 19% boost in SP skill valuation and a favorable right-handed platoon advantage, making him our primary engine for both counting stats and potential SB opportunities. Similarly, **Jose Caballero** (72.91) serves as a high-upside play in the bottom of the order; while his position in the lineup is suboptimal, his 86% SB-efficiency against the slow-delivery Springs makes him an essential inclusion to address our scarcity in stolen bases.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was excluding **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, who registered a strong baseline projection but ultimately missed the cut due to his current status outside the active starting lineup. Our remaining exposure is balanced by the power potential of **Giancarlo Stanton** (68.81), who thrives against Springs despite the neutral platoon, and **Max Muncy** (59.95). **Max Muncy** remains a viable start against Weathers, with his score buoyed by park factors and the green light to run against a susceptible battery. Conversely, **Vinnie Pasquantino** (53.94) and **Tyler Soderstrom** (55.94) are relegated to marginal status; both are hampered by dynamic platoon disadvantages against left-handed starters, leaving **Zach McKinstry** (48.81) as a bare-minimum filler to round out the outfield.\n\nLooking ahead, we are closely monitoring the rest status of our core pieces like **Corbin Carroll**, **Austin Riley**, **Seiya Suzuki**, and **Trevor Story**, as well as the developing profiles of **Brice Turang**, **Gabriel Moreno**, **Dalton Rushing**, **Alex Freeland**, **Kyle Karros**, **Carson Williams**, **Gabriel Arias**, and **Travis Bazzana**. With **Josh Naylor** and **James Wood** sidelined by scheduling off-days, our bench depth is intentionally thin today to ensure we don't bleed game caps on low-probability outcomes. We are playing for maximum efficiency in the SB category; proceed with these assignments until official lineup confirmations force a pivot.",
